Description: Meta Overlay Manager - install packages without root access
 mom allows non-root users to install and update packages on systems where
 they lack root access. It wraps apt-get (Debian/Ubuntu) and dnf (RHEL)
 with a security-hardened setuid binary.
 .
 A sysadmin deploys it once; authorized users (members of the "mom" group)
 can then install packages without sudo or root access. All operations are
 logged to a JSON audit log and syslog.
 .
 Security features include complete environment sanitization, strict package
 name validation, a configurable deny list with glob pattern support,
 hardcoded package manager paths, and supplemental group dropping.
